{"id": 4256, "title": "Ticket #4256: param self-references to pre-defined param values don't work", "description": "<blockquote>\nNormally, when the parameter in the config file refers to itself the self-reference is substituted at config load time. so\n\n<p></p><pre>    foo = 2\n    foo = $(foo) + 1\n</pre>\n\n<p>in the second line above, <code>$(foo)</code> will be replaced with 2 at the time the config file is read, and <code>foo -&gt; 2 + 1</code> will be written into the config table.  But when the current value of <code>foo</code> comes from param_info.in instead of an earlier line in the config file, then $(foo) will be substituted with \"\" instead of the pre-defined foo.\n\n</p><p>The result is that config file params can't build on pre-defined values for the same param.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Aug-08 12:11</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/5ac3cf34185447d6ff37b5999b392ef65eea4c1d\">[40922]</a></span>: AF_UNIX by any other name... <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=4256\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4256'); return false;\" title=\"param self-references to pre-defined param values don't work\">#4256</a></span>  (By Brian Bockelman )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Mar-31 13:06</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/c52c9c19034fcdcce38eac39ef6489